==Japanese==
{{ja-kanjitab|家|内}}
===Etymology===
Literally ‘inside the house’ from the Sino-Japanese (on'yomi) readings of 家 (''ka'', ‘house’) and 内 (''nai'', ‘inside’).

===Noun===
{{ja-noun|k|hira=かない|rom=kanai}}
# (one's own) [[wife]]

===Synonyms===
* [[妻]] (つま, tsuma)
* [[奥さん]] (おくさん, okusan)

===Usage notes===
This word should only be used in reference to the speaker's own wife, where as okusan (奥さん) is a polite term used to refer to someone else's wife. Tsuma (妻) is a more general term for a wife, and can also mean spouse.